OL,4,Cschools to be lifted under government
OL,5,Cplans
OL,7,FThe Right Reverend Marcus Stock,
OL,8,FBishop of Leeds and chairman of the
OL,9,FCatholic Education Service (CES),
OL,10,Fsaid: "These proposals are welcome.
OL,11,FDioceses are well placed to respond to
OL,12,Fdiffering local educational demands
OL,13,Faround the country, including the
OL,14,Fprovision for children with special
OL,15,Feducational needs and disabilities.
OL,16,FParents can welcome this also."
OL,18,FHe added that Catholic education
OL,19,F"provides a high performing school
OL,20,Fsector and promotes the formation of
OL,21,Fchildren in values and virtues".
